items.title: LOS GATOS TREEHOUSE
items.description: Cathie Hong had been an interior designer for years. So when the mom of four kids embarked on renovating her own family’s new home—a moody, redwood-clad, midcentury residence tucked behind trees in Los Gatos, California—she thought she had it on lock. But the process proved to be a surprising one: “The whole experience of renovating my house was eye-opening for me. I thought going into it that I would know exactly what to do because I’m always working with my clients on their renovation projects,” Hong explains. “It was very different being the homeowner!”
